33:
After those seven years ended, I, Nebuchadnezzar, looked up toward heaven and acknowledged that what God said was true. Then I could think correctly again, and my sanity was restored. I praised and worshiped the Most High, and I honored him, the one who lives forever.\q1 He rules forever;
\q2 his ruling power is an everlasting authority.


\q1

34:
He regards all the people in the world as insignificant.\q1 He has the power to do whatever he wants to do.
\q2 He does whatever he wants with the angel armies in heaven and with us who live on the earth.
\q1 So no one can correct him;
\q2 no one can challenge him;
\q2 no one can say to him, "Why are you doing these things?"


